<div id="review_3966527664" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3966527664" />
    <a title="Layla" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/109681904-layla"><img alt="Layla" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623962676p2/109681904.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3966527664?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Layla" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Layla" href="/user/show/109681904-layla">Layla</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3966527664" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10244087458330652922"><b>~ 3.55 stars ~</b><br/><br/>Confirmed: My heart is made out of ice. <br/><br/>I do wish I could say that I felt more emotion than I actually did by that ending, but alas, I cannot. I did still quite enjoy this book though, but to be fair, the bar was low to begin with. I found this collection of novellas entertaining and I was glad to have gotten more of Celaena’s backstory. Of course, there were varying degrees of how good each individual novella is, but overall, a solid read. <br/><br/><br/><br/><b><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3953499204?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Assassin and the Pirate Lord</a> ★★★☆☆ (3</b></span>
  <span id="freeText10244087458330652922" style="display:none"><b>~ 3.55 stars ~</b><br><br>Confirmed: My heart is made out of ice. <br><br>I do wish I could say that I felt more emotion than I actually did by that ending, but alas, I cannot. I did still quite enjoy this book though, but to be fair, the bar was low to begin with. I found this collection of novellas entertaining and I was glad to have gotten more of Celaena’s backstory. Of course, there were varying degrees of how good each individual novella is, but overall, a solid read. <br><br><br><br><b><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3953499204?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1" rel="nofollow noopener">The Assassin and the Pirate Lord</a> ★★★☆☆ (3 stars)</b><br><br>Not bad. A decent start to the story. I finally met Sam and exploring his relationship and dynamic with Celaena was interesting. It is definitely not the strongest one and I’m not sure if I gained as much as I would have liked from this, but I understand that it is essential for the rest. All the redundant exclamation marks have made a return, which I am not a fan of, but the voice in my head that acts this all out sounds so ridiculous when it reads a sentence that ends with one, that it is actually funny, so there is that. <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1620110750i/31278567._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><a href="https://morgana0anagrom.tumblr.com/post/611201767271792640/finally-can-share-this-wohoo-this-piece-was-done" rel="nofollow noopener">credit</a><br><br><br><b><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3966542345?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1" rel="nofollow noopener">The Assassin and the Healer</a> ★★☆☆☆ +½ (2.5 stars)</b><br><br>My least favorite out of them all. It was pretty boring not going to lie. I expected much more, and ultimately it was a let down. Not saying it was necessarily bad, no, there was nothing super wrong with it, I just wasn’t immersed into the story and was ready for it to be over. I am looking forward to seeing how Yrene is incorporated into the main books.<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1607021845i/30466685._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><a href="https://morgana0anagrom.tumblr.com/post/611201767271792640/finally-can-share-this-wohoo-this-piece-was-done" rel="nofollow noopener">credit</a><br><br><b><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3966723220?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1" rel="nofollow noopener">The Assassin and the Desert</a> ★★★★☆ +¼ (4.25 stars)</b><br><br>Undeniably a level up from the first two. I loved the setting, I liked the new additions, and I loved the character development and depth we got from Celaena and I found Ansel to be a pretty good character. I liked her despite the ending. It was a fun time, not much else to say here other than this gave me high hopes for the remaining two. <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1620111073i/31278571._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><a href="https://morgana0anagrom.tumblr.com/post/611201767271792640/finally-can-share-this-wohoo-this-piece-was-done" rel="nofollow noopener">credit</a><br><br><br><b><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3968465574?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Assassin and the Underworld</a> ★★★★☆ +½ (4.5 stars)</b><br><br>This one is my favorite and the most entertaining. And we did get to know Sam much more then before, which I will admit, upon starting these novellas, I expected to have more content with him. Though I have no big critiques for this, the writing style, which isn't my favorite, will always stop me from giving a complete five star rating. <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1606972027i/30463228._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><a href="https://www.instagram.com/bxromance/?igshid=ml6qsbsj0xka" rel="nofollow noopener">credit</a><br><br><br><b><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3969849282?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Assassin and the Empire</a> ★★★☆☆ +½ (3.5 stars)</b><br><br>Good, but underwhelming. This was a let down, especially plot wise and when it came to the emotional aspect. Since it’s 3rd perspective, I feel as if it missed an opportunity to truly end on the right note by not giving Sam a chapter for his POV, that would have definitely added to affect. But really, it was good, I liked how it ended leading up to the first Throne of Glass book, I just didn't find it to be up to par with the 2 before. <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1620111658i/31278582._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><a href="https://arz28art.tumblr.com/" rel="nofollow noopener">credit</a><br><br><br><i><b>Average:</b> ★★★☆☆ +.55 (3.55 stars)</i><br><br><b>Final Thoughts:</b> Not bad, much better than I had anticipated it to be, and pleasantly so. Honestly, I don’t know where this energy was during the first three Throne of Glass books (the only I have read so far) and I am excited to continue on with the series and see what is in store.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10244087458330652922" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

